The issue you&#39;re is due to Kotlin&#39;s type inference not working as expected in this specific context when using lambdas with Java functional interfaces.

To address this, you can explicitly declare the lambda type using the `Function` interface in your code:

```kotlin
import java.util.function.Function

fun main() {
   val s: Function&lt;String, String&gt; = Function&lt;String, String&gt; { s -&gt; s + s }
   // Or simply 
   // val s: Function&lt;String, String&gt; = Function { s -&gt; s + s }
}
```

Try to use `Function&lt;String, String&gt;`, full example:

    import java.util.function.Function
    
    fun main() {
        val s: Function&lt;String, String&gt; = Function { s -&gt; s + s }
        val result = s.apply(&quot;Kotlin&quot;)
        println(result) // KotlinKotlin
    }

